Bayer USA Inc said sales of itsaffiliated operating cmpanies based in the U.S. increased in1986 by 4.4 pct from the previous year.    Combined sales were 4.2 billion dlrs, up from 4.0 billiondlrs in 1985, the company said.    However, the company said net income was 106.9 mln dlrs,three pct below 1985.    Bayer said its operating companies include Mobay Corp,Miles Laboratories Inc, Agfa-Gevaert Inc, Compugraphic Corp,Haarmann and Reimer Corp, Deerfield Urethane Inc and HelenaChemical Co.    Bayer said Mobay, its primary chemicals company, reportednet income of 83.4 mln dlrs, up eight pct of 1985. It also saidMiles, its pharmaceutical and healthcare company, recordednet income of 29 mln dlrs, a 44 pct increase over 1985.    Reuter&#3;